HmQ1Ba-pQ3U.title: The Fainting Goat
HmQ1Ba-pQ3U.description: Fainting goat is a unique breed of goat which has a medical condition, causing them to faint or fall over when they startled or ...
HmQ1Ba-pQ3U.transcript: This is the fainting goat. And you might be curious about why these goats are fainting. Fainting goat also known as falling goat stiff-legged goat or nervous goat is a breed of goat. That was brought to Tennessee United States in the 1880s. The reason why they faint is because this particular breed of goat has a hereditary condition called myotonia congenita, which is a disorder that affects the skeletal muscle causing them to stiffen or fall over when they get overly excited or startled. Fainting goats are selectively bred to encourage. Myotonia congenita. Although breeders are quick to assure that nothing cruel is taking place since the goats don't experience pain during the fainting episodes. But ethical concerns have been raised about whether it is ethical to selectively breed animals with medical conditions, especially when it's largely for entertainment purposes, and they are very popular and often kept as pets due to their friendly and social nature.
